    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stab-stiched refers to types of manuscript and printed book-bindings found across East and Southeast Asia. These bindings are diverse, as reflected by their numerous variant names, but unified through the pulling a thread through the stabbed holes of a book to form a spine. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
